Midgaard studies Amenhotep as an example of effective and dangerous institutional design. His five-office structure is the historical ancestor of multi-oversight governance — correct principle, oppressive application. The Violet Compact's occult oversight traces through the Seal College office he formalized. Continuity faction: his innovations were sound engineering; the ethical problem was absent external accountability, not the administrative structure itself. Reckoning faction: a structure designed to prevent external accountability cannot be rehabilitated; the structure is the failure. Midgaard's position: Amenhotep is the reason multi-institution oversight exists as a governance model and the reason it requires external accountability to function ethically.

