Khenari descent-records from the Solar Court period document the consequences of Amenhotep's surveillance-documentation merger on mortuary records. Under his design, Embalmer Houses held theological rather than legal authority over death records; Khenari legal identity was therefore dependent on a theologically administered system. When the Solar Court fractured, Embalmer House records lost authority simultaneously with institutional support — a structural vulnerability his design created. Khenari descent-record practitioners cite this as the reason they maintain independent documentation outside any single institution's control. The lesson: death records must have multiple custodians, not secular custodians. Khenari position: Amenhotep built one of the most complete death-record systems in the corridor's history and ensured it would not survive him.

